@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    Shop Management System
    Developed by Rezaul Karim
    Last Updated: March 03, 2026
    <br />
    <br />
    Rezaul Karim (“we”, “us”, or “our”) operates the Shop Management System (the “System” or “Service”), a web-based shop management application built with ASP.NET Core MVC. The System helps shop owners manage inventory, sales, customers, employees, billing, and reports.
    <br />
    <br />
    This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal data when you use the Service. It applies to all users (shop owners, employees, and any individuals whose data is entered into the System).
    <br />
    <br />
    By accessing or using the System, you consent to the practices described in this Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
    <br />
    <br />
    1. Information We Collect
    We collect the following categories of information:
    A. Information You Provide Directly

    Account & registration data: name, email address, phone number, password, business name, shop address, trade license/BIN (if provided).
    Shop operational data: inventory details, sales records, purchase records.
    Customer data (entered by you): customer name, phone, address, purchase history (you as the shop owner are the data controller for your customers’ data).
    Employee data (if added): name, phone, role, salary details.
    Payment & billing information: bank details or payment gateway information for subscription fees (processed via third-party gateways like SSLCommerz, bKash, etc.).
    <br />
    <br />

    B. Automatically Collected Information

    Device and usage data: IP address, browser type, device ID, operating system, pages visited, time spent, and clickstream data.
    Cookies and similar technologies (see Section 9).
    Server logs and error reports.
    <br />
    <br />

    C. Information from Third Parties

    Payment processors or authentication providers (Google, Microsoft, etc.) when you sign up using their services.
    <br />
    <br />

    2. How We Use Your Information
    We use the collected information to:

    Provide, maintain, and improve the Shop Management System (including hosting, backups, and updates).
    Process your subscription payments and send billing receipts.
    Communicate with you (service updates, support tickets, newsletters – you can opt out).
    Generate reports, analytics, and insights for your shop.
    Detect fraud, security issues, and enforce our Terms of Service.
    Comply with legal obligations under Bangladeshi law.

    We act as a data processor for any customer or employee data you upload. You (the shop owner) remain the data controller and are responsible for obtaining necessary consents from your customers and employees.
    <br />
    <br />

    3. Legal Basis for Processing (under PDPO 2025)
    We rely on:

    Your consent (where required).
    Performance of a contract (providing the Service).
    Legitimate business interests (improving the Service, security).
    Legal compliance (tax, accounting, or government requests).
    <br />
    <br />

    4. How We Share or Disclose Your Information
    We do not sell your personal data. We may share data only in these cases:

    Service Providers: Cloud hosting (e.g., Azure, AWS), payment gateways, email service providers – all under strict data processing agreements.
    Legal Requirements: When required by court order, government authority, or under the Personal Data Protection Ordinance 2025 (PDPO 2025), Cyber Security Act, or other Bangladeshi laws.
    Business Transfer: In case of merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.
    With Your Consent: For any other purpose you explicitly approve.
    <br />
    <br />

    5. Data Security
    We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures, including:

    Encryption of data in transit (HTTPS) and at rest.
    Role-based access control in the ASP.NET Core MVC application.
    Regular security audits and updates.
    Secure password storage (hashed and salted).

    In the event of a data breach, we will notify affected users and the relevant Bangladeshi authority as required by PDPO 2025 (generally within 72 hours where feasible).
    <br />
    <br />

    6. Data Retention
    We retain your data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined or as required by law (e.g., 6–7 years for accounting records). You may request deletion of your account data at any time (subject to legal obligations).
    
    <br />
    <br />

    7. Your Rights under the Personal Data Protection Ordinance 2025 (PDPO 2025)
    As a data subject, you have the right to:

    Access, correct, or delete your personal data.
    Withdraw consent.
    Restrict or object to processing.
    Data portability (receive your data in a structured format).
    Lodge a complaint with the National Data Governance & Integrity Authority (or the designated regulator under PDPO 2025).
    <br />
    <br />

    To exercise these rights, email us at the address in Section 12. We will respond within 03 days (or as per PDPO timelines).
    <br />
    <br />

    8. International Data Transfers
    The System may use cloud servers located outside Bangladesh (e.g., Singapore, USA). When transferring data, we ensure appropriate safeguards (Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent measures) as required by PDPO 2025.
    <br />
    <br />

    9. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
    We use essential cookies for login sessions and functionality. Analytics cookies (e.g., via Google Analytics or similar) help us understand usage. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings. A cookie consent banner is displayed on first visit.
    <br />
    <br />

    10. Children’s Privacy
    The Service is not intended for individuals under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If we become aware of such data, we will delete it.
    <br />
    <br />

    11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
    We may update this Policy from time to time. The “Last Updated” date will be revised. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new Policy. We will notify significant changes via email or in-app notice.
    <br />
    <br />

    12. Contact Us
    For any questions, requests, or complaints regarding this Privacy Policy or your data:
